(nICacheWays, DCacheMiss).explanation: Instruction cache associativity and data cache misses operate on different memory hierarchies and do not directly influence each other;

(nICacheWays, nDCacheMSHRs).explanation: Instruction cache associativity and data cache MSHR configuration are independent architectural parameters that do not causally affect each other;

(nICacheWays, ICacheMiss).explanation: Higher instruction cache associativity reduces conflict misses by providing more placement options for cache lines, thereby decreasing the frequency of instruction cache misses;
